  <h1>Cybersecurity Newsfeed</h1>
  <h2>📅 01/08/25</h2>

  <h2>🛡️ Vulnerabilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Active exploitation of CVE-2025-5394 in the Alone WordPress theme enables unauthenticated RCE via ZIP uploads. Patched in 7.8.5. <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/180630/hacking/attackers-actively-exploit-critical-zero-day-in-alone-wordpress-theme.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
    <li>CISA disclosed six vulnerabilities in Honeywell Experion PKS affecting pre-R520.2 and R530 versions. Flaws allow RCE and DoS on critical infrastructure. <a href="https://www.securityweek.com/honeywell-experion-pks-flaws-allow-manipulation-of-industrial-processes/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🎯 Adversaries</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Russia-linked APT Secret Blizzard (Turla) targets embassies in Moscow with ISP-level AiTM attacks using ApolloShadow malware. <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/180638/apt/russia-linked-apt-secret-blizzard-targets-foreign-embassies-in-moscow-with-apolloshadow-malware.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
    <li>Epsilon Red ransomware spreads via fake Discord, Twitch, and OnlyFans verification pages using .HTA files and ActiveX abuse. <a href="https://hackread.com/onlyfans-discord-clickfix-pages-epsilon-red-ransomware/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
    <li>Malicious Chrome extensions can hijack conversations from ChatGPT, Claude, Copilot, and Gemini to steal corporate data. <a href="https://www.zdnet.com/article/malicious-extensions-can-use-chatgpt-to-steal-your-personal-data-heres-how/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
    <li>Scattered Spider halts activity after four UK arrests. Mandiant notes their recent use of RattyRAT, DragonForce, and AiTM TTPs. <a href="https://www.infosecurity-magazine.com/news/cybercriminals-spooked-scattered/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
    <li>Lazarus Group distributed over 200 malicious npm and PyPI packages to steal secrets and infiltrate CI/CD systems in a large-scale espionage campaign. <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2025/07/alert-fatigue-data-overload-and-fall-of.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📈 Trends</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Secret Blizzard’s use of Russia’s SORM and ISP-level MITM confirms a new stage in APT-level surveillance and diplomatic espionage. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/microsoft-russian-hackers-use-isp-access-to-hack-embassies-in-aitm-attacks/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
    <li>GreyNoise: 80% of new CVE disclosures follow malicious scanning spikes within six weeks—often by probing known vendor vulnerabilities. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/spikes-in-malicious-activity-precede-new-cves-in-80-percent-of-cases/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📂 Breach/Leaks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Everest ransomware claims Mailchimp breach with 767MB of marketing and CRM data. No confirmation yet from Mailchimp. <a href="https://hackread.com/everest-ransomware-claims-mailchimp-small-breach/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

